ce:section.ce:para:
For determining the feasibility of the immunosensor towards human serum sample, recovery test was conducted. The human serum sample was spiked with different concentrations of HPV-16L1 antigen such as 0.1 ng/µL, 1 ng/µL, 10 ng/µL, 50 ng/µL and the electrochemical studies were performed. On increasing the concentration from 0.1 ng/µL to 50 ng/µL, a decrease in peak current (Fig. S8 (A,B)) and an increase in Rct was observed (Fig. 9
                        ). This depicts the efficient binding of HPV-16L1 antigen onto the sensor electrode from the spiked serum sample. Also, the recovery percentage was got to be in the range of 91 % to 98 % as shown in Table 2
                        . This indicates that the prepared immunosensor is well suited for real sample analysis and can be well applied in the quantitative detection of HPV-16L1 in human serums.
